{
  "stem": "18960.2",
  "chunk_idx": 6,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 10.0,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "So I took the last train from Lwow to Drohobycz [PAUSES FOR 5 SECONDS] before the outbreak of the war, because I saw a lot of-- a lot of border police in-- in Lwow, with green-- with green caps on their heads.",
      "word_count": 42
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And I saw a bad omen in it.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And I decided to leave.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "And I came home to my uncle, to Drohobycz.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "It was a Saturday night.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And Sunday morning, the war broke out.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And there was a few days that the Russians-- a few days after the outbreak of the war, the Russians gave up.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "They ran away.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "The Russian army ran away back east, and there were a few days we were left.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "There were no-- no Germans yet, and no Russians.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "At that time, I was back in Schodnica.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "I went back home.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "We had nothing to do with Drohobycz anymore.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "Matter of fact, my uncle Moses, with his-- with his son came back-- went back with me to Schodnica, hoping that Schodnica is a safe place to hide in case-- in case there's trouble.",
      "word_count": 34
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "Because they had trusted the Ukrainian population there.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "With they-- they had close relationship with the Jewish people at the time.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "Little did they know what's going to happen.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "When I came back to Schodnica at the time and I looked at those Ukrainian faces, I predicted that something is going to happen.",
      "word_count": 24
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 15,
      "text": "And I-- we had a little, like a cellar outside, next to the barn.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 16,
      "text": "That cellar was built like this.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 17,
      "text": "Was built-- it had concrete walls, then covered with sod.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 18,
      "text": "And there-- and around the sod with a wooden structure.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 19,
      "text": "So I-- a few days after-- after-- before the Germans came, I made like a-- a hideaway there, a hiding place, in that cellar.",
      "word_count": 24
    }
  ],
